You   have   a   table   called   Customer   and   an   attribute   cust_name.   Update   the   customer's   who's   name   is   'Sam'   to   'Samuel'.

Options:

INSERT   into   Customer   table
Values   ('Samuel);

UPDATE   table
cust_name   =   'Samuel';

UPDATE   Customer
set   customer   'Sam'
TO   'Samuel';

UPDATE   Customer
SET   cust_name   =   'Samuel'
WHERE   cust_name   =   'Sam';

Choose   the   correct   command   to   change   to   another   container/pdb:

Options:

alter   pluggable   database   set   container   =   pdb_name;

alter   session   set   container   =   pdb_name;

alter   pluggable   database   set   session   =pdb_name;

alter   pluggable   database   set   container   pdb_name;

Which   command   is   used   for   opening   a   pluggable   database?

Options:

alter   database   open;

alter   database   <name   0f   pdb>   open

alter   pluggable   database   <name   of   pdb>   open;

alter   pluggable   database   =   open;

The correct option is:

alter pluggable database <name of pdb> open;

The ALTER PLUGGABLE DATABASE command is used to modify and perform administrative tasks on a pluggable database (PDB) in a container database (CDB). To open a specific PDB, the command is:

ALTER PLUGGABLE DATABASE <PDB name> OPEN;

This command will open the specified PDB in the current container database instance.
